[msg msg_combine_HELP_KIHON_0_3 [Caroline]]
Still, you can choose some skills from[n]the original Personas for the new[n]Persona to inherit.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KIHON_0_4 [Justine]]
Newly summoned Personas will learn[n]skills as they become stronger.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KIHON_0_5 [Caroline]]
In other words, you can eventually make[n]a Persona with all the skills you want.
If you're willing to put in the time,[n]that is!

[msg msg_combine_HELP_COPY [Justine]]
Usually, when you fuse Personas, the[n]Personas you combine are sacrificed in[n]the process.
However, if you select to "copy" a[n]Persona, we will duplicate that Persona[n]before it vanishes.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_COPY_02 [Caroline]]
That way, even if you fuse the Persona[n]you have equipped, it won't vanish on[n]you.
Of course, copying isn't free.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_COPY_03 [Justine]]
It is up to you to use this option[n]wisely.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_COPY_04 [Caroline]]
If you want to copy Personas, select it[n]when you're choosing what to fuse.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_RULE [Caroline]]
It looks like a fusion result is based[n]on the Arcana of the Personas used in[n]the fusion.
Well, I hear there are a couple that[n]don't really follow that rule...

[msg msg_combine_HELP_RULE_02 [Justine]]
One such outlier would be if you fused[n]two Personas of the same Arcana.
We understand that if two Personas of[n]identical Arcana are fused, the[n]resulting one will be one rank lower.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_RULE_03 [Caroline]]
Either way, just try out a bunch of[n]different combinations and learn it[n]yourself!

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KEISYOU [Justine]]
A Persona born from a fusion may inherit[n]the skills of the Personas used to[n]create it.
In other words, you can use fusion to[n]teach a Persona skills that it could[n]never learn on its own.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KEISYOU_2 [Caroline]]
It's the most important part of making a[n]strong Persona, so get it in your head.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KEISYOU_3 [Justine]]
We aren't sure of all the particulars[n]behind inheritance, but there are three[n]basic rules:
First, you can select which skills get[n]passed down.
Second, the Persona being fused may have[n]limits on which skills it can inherit.
...We can speak more on that topic[n]shortly.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_KEISYOU_4 [Caroline]]
Last: the more skills the combined[n]Personas have, the more skills the new[n]one gets to inherit!
You'll probably learn better from trying[n]it yourself. Get to it, Inmate.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_ZOKUSEI [Justine]]
Let me give you more details on skill[n]inheritance.
Each Persona has skills that can and[n]cannot be inherited.
These are determined by the Persona's[n]characteristics.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_ZOKUSEI_2 [Caroline]]
We'll tell you some of what we've found[n]so far, so listen up.
Personas that are good at physical[n]attacks can't inherit healing skills...
So, it figures that healer Personas[n]wouldn't learn physical attack skills!

[msg msg_combine_HELP_ZOKUSEI_3 [Justine]]
Fire and Ice, Bless and Curse... Some[n]affinities are paired so.
Personas favoring a certain affinity[n]cannot inherit skills of its opposite.
Thus, you know what a Persona cannot[n]learn by studying its starting skills.

[msg msg_combine_HELP_ZOKUSEI_4 [Caroline]]
There are exceptions, though.
